               <item n="project_comment_old">&lt;p&gt;[[Broomhead I]]: 240-241 translates: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a1 [He] sees those who have become buddhas, from all the happy ones &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a2 [He] will enjoy all the good things again [and] yet full of misery [are these ones] (Pl.N.?) &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a3 Until he crosses over the river. He who [is] in the river Kṣāranadī &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a4 [And] there the life-flood (water) is &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a5 In thousands and tens of thousands, the earth, the nāgas (dragons) [and] the snakes ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b1 The good deeds destroy by preference [and] through envy [there is] ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b2 Meditation becomes apparent [and] his meditation [is] ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b3 And immediately afterwards the most excellent water &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b4 And [they] attain happiness [and good fortune], and right up to this (life)-water ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b5 [And they] come forth [and begin to] (gather) just a little food from the trees. &lt;/p&gt;</item>
